column5: Spent a few hours riding the waves today in search of some Pike , we even broke down and tried for perch to elude the skunk , but no luck.  we launched from Orillia and worked the north end , even a quick trip into Couch didn't help. TB
Ah that hurts never heard you report a Skunk Tinbanger why don't you join us Nove 14th 15th 16th on the Bay of Quinte G2G for some big eyes and bring Pikie with ya like too meet you guys.
thats why I don't don't report much LOL!  Have  a wedding that weekend but sure you guys will have a blast. Pikeie is at school in the Soo right now , getting his fill of salmon  TB
skunk...don't like to use that word...how about a nice day on the water uninterrupted by slimy fish
Yah Terry... you'd hope there was enough fish smell in the boat so he couldn't smell the skunk. I know in mine all I can smell is that Shithead you slimmed the boat with last year on BOQ
Terry ,for sure last sk--k cracked my trailer fender on the way to GBAY couple week back, come to think of it , no fish in the boat since. Coincidence ?  TB
